section.section:
Paragraph (2) of this subsection does not apply to:
The City of Annapolis;
Any transfer or assignment of a license located within the 1,000-foot requirement;
Any nonprofit club or nonprofit organization;
Any restaurant destroyed by fire, flood, windstorm or any other act of God and which held a valid alcoholic beverage license at the time it was destroyed if a new church or school has not been constructed within the 1,000-foot requirement;
Any Class H beer and wine license (on-sale) or Class H beer, wine and liquor license (on-sale); or
Any motel-restaurant complex, hotel-restaurant complex, beer, wine and liquor license (on-sale).
